<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6f3fc65-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57514"><num value="57514">§ 57514.</num><heading> Qualifications of bidders</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6f3fc66-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57514/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Considerations</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>In deciding whether to award a charter to a bidder, the Secretary of Transportation shall consider—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f3fc67-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57514/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the bidder’s financial resources, credit standing, and practical experience in operating vessels; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6f3fc68-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57514/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> other factors a prudent business person would consider in entering into a transaction involving a large capital investment.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6f3fc69-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s57514/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Disqualifications</inline>.—</heading><content>The Secretary may not charter a vessel to a person appearing to lack sufficient capital, credit, and experience to operate the vessel successfully over the period covered by the charter.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6f3fc6a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1666">120 Stat. 1666</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
